  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Pangea Pod Hotel is a unique capsule hotel concept that provides the personal space of a boutique hotel and the social vibe of a hostel. It’s a hub in the heart of Whistler Village where guests can meet like-minded travellers and socialise with friends, yet still have their own personal space to retire to (and get quality sleep in) at the end of each day.</p>
<h2><span>Social Scene</span></h2>
<p>Pangea is central, social, and affordable. Their on-site café/bar, The Living Room, is the ideal place to grab a gourmet coffee or craft beer. Try out their popular après and signature cocktails on Whistler's only rooftop patio bar.</p>
<h2>The Pods</h2>
<p>All of Pangea’s designer pods include a double bed with privacy curtain, as well as USB charging points, hangers, towels and linens, LED lighting, and a personal fan. Suites are male and female mixed dorms.</p>
<p>Enjoy your day on the slopes knowing your things are safely stored with lockable cubbies in each pod and secure ski/snowboard storage (for more information on security please see our Facilities tab below).</p>
<p>Each of Pangea’s bathrooms is separated into four individually accessed components, including a shower cabin, bathroom with sink, changing room, and stand-alone vanity with backlit mirror.</p>
<h2>Location</h2>
<p>The hotel has an unbeatable location in the centre of the pedestrianised Village Stroll. All of Whistler's best restaurants, cafes, and bars are within easy reach, and Whistler Blackcomb’s gondolas are just a couple minutes' walk away.</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
